-- AL East-Leading Orioles Defeat Rays 4-3 on Johnson’s 2-Run Homer
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-05-12T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-12/al-east-leading-orioles-defeat-rays-4-3-on-johnson-s-2-run-homer.html
Nick Johnson hit a two-run homer in
the seventh inning to give the American League East-leading
Baltimore Orioles a 4-3 victory over the  Tampa Bay Rays  in a
Major League Baseball contest.  Luke Scott scored as Sean Rodriguez grounded into a double
play in the second inning for the Rays (20-13), followed by  Adam Jones ’s solo homer to even the score at 1-1 at Oriole Park at
Camden Yards.  Elliot Johnson had a run-scoring single and  Carlos Pena 
walked with the bases loaded to score Jose Molina in the fourth
inning to give the Rays a 3-1 advantage.  Nick Markakis hit his sixth home run of the season in the
sixth inning as the Orioles (21-12) trailed 3-2 before Johnson
batted in two runs in the seventh.  Darren O’Day (3-0) threw a perfect seventh inning for the
Orioles. Jim Johnson had a perfect ninth for his 10th save.  Joel Peralta (0-2) allowed one run on one hit in 1/3
inning.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  